						               													<description>Igel und Floh (&amp;quot;Hedgehog and Flea&amp;quot;) new game from their Clever Kiddo series that features a &amp;quot;spiel + buch&amp;quot;-- game and book, with book's text being in German.  Obviously geared towards younger players, it appears to be an &amp;quot;alphabet game&amp;quot; that engages players with colorful cards and pictures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This unusual game helps children to learn their first letters and words. The book can be read out loud by children under 5 years of age.  Children are playfully introduced to the 5 vowels.  The letters become objectives in a story.  Chopsticks and rings are attached to the lovingly illustrated book, with which one can append the vowels.  There are 55 cards depicting the entire alphabet.  Using the cards, simple words can be added to the pictures to create imaginative stories.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
